8 Section 3. Section 76-2-304, MCA, is amended to read:
9 "76-2-304. Criteria and guidelines for zoning regulations. (1) Zoning regulations must be:
10 (a) made in accordance with a growth policy; and
11 (b) designed to:
12 (i) secure safety from fire and other dangers;
13 (ii) promote public health, public safety, and the general welfare; and
14 (iii) facilitate the adequate provision of transportation, water, sewerage, schools, parks, and other
15 public requirements.
16 (2) In the adoption of zoning regulations, the municipal governing body shall consider:
17 (a) reasonable provision of adequate light and air;
18 (b) the effect on motorized and nonmotorized transportation systems;
19 (c) promotion of compatible urban growth;
20 (d) the character of the district and its peculiar suitability for particular uses; and
21 (e) conserving the value of buildings and encouraging the most appropriate use of land throughout
22 the jurisdictional area.
23 (3) In a city with a population of at least 5,000 residents, duplex housing must be allowed as a
24 permitted use on a lot where a single-family residence is a permitted use, and zoning regulations that apply to
25 the development or use of duplex housing may not be more restrictive than zoning regulations that are
26 applicable to single-family residences.
27 (4) (a) In a municipality that is designated as an urban area by the United States census bureau
28 with a population over 5,000 as of the most recent census, the city council or other legislative body of the
